        'title' => 'Managing Buildings and Rooms',
      ),
      'value' => '<p>The Conference Manager can create one or more buildings, each with one or more rooms. To create a building the Conference Manager has to click the Scheduler link, then the Buildings and Rooms link followed by the Create New Building link. The Conference Manager must assign the new building a name and abbreviation, and can enter an optional description. Buildings that have been added to the system can be edited, deleted, and arranged for sort order from the Buildings and Rooms page.</p>  
		<p>For each building there is also a Rooms link: clicking this will display a list of rooms associated to that building, with a link to Create a New Room at the bottom of the page. The Conference Manager must provide a name and abbreviation for each room, and can provide an optional description as well. Again, rooms that have been added to the system can be edited, deleted and arranged for display purposes from the Rooms page.</p>
		<p>It is advisable to add directions to the description of any buildings and rooms added to the system: these directions will be available from the Conference Schedule page.</p>
		<p>Special events cannot be assigned a building/room location, so such locations should not be entered into the system.</p>',
